## General

- Prefer readability over brevity; descriptive function and variable names
- In comments/logs, explain "why" in Turkish; avoid inline noise
- Keep line width reasonable; avoid horizontal scrolling

## AutoLISP Style (src/**/*.lsp)

- Function names: English, verb-phrase where appropriate
- Variables: English, descriptive
- Comments: Turkish
- Handle errors with `vl-catch-all-apply` where needed; never leave global state dirty

Example:
```lisp
; Polylinelerden spline üretir ve orijinal objeyi saklar
(defun c:PolylineToCurve (/ sel)
  (setq sel (ssget "_X" '((0 . "LWPOLYLINE"))))
  (if sel
    (progn (prompt "\nSeçim bulundu") (princ))
    (prompt "\nPolyline bulunamadı"))
  (princ))
```

## PowerShell Style (scripts/*.ps1)

- Non-interactive by default; add `-WhatIf` and `-Confirm:$false` where safe
- Use `Write-Host`/`Write-Output` with concise Turkish messages

## Markdown Docs (docs/**)

- User-facing docs in Turkish; include short runnable examples

